        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(memory-core): write ## Deep Sleep summary to DREAMS.md",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Problem: The Deep Sleep phase writes per-phase report files (`memory/dreaming/deep/YYYY-MM-DD.md`) but never writes the documented `## Deep Sleep` summary section to `DREAMS.md`. Per docs: \"Deep phase writes a `## Deep Sleep` summary into `DREAMS.md` and optionally writes `memory/dreaming/deep/YYYY-MM-DD.md`.\"\n- What changed: `writeDeepDreamingReport` now always writes the `## Deep Sleep` summary to `DREAMS.md`. When an existing `## Deep Sleep` section is present, it is replaced in-place (including when the heading appears at file position 0 without a leading newline). Other sections in DREAMS.md are preserved. The separate per-phase report file is still conditionally written when storage mode requests it. Added test coverage for separateReports=false (DREAMS.md only) and section replacement (non-destructive, no duplicates).\n\n## Change Type\n\n- [x] Bug fix\n\n## Linked Issues\n\n- Closes #91051\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** Deep Sleep phase never writes `## Deep Sleep` to DREAMS.md (#91051).\n\n**Real environment tested:** Node v22.22.0, Linux x86_64.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\nOPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=4 pnpm test -- extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming-markdown.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming-phases.test.ts\n\n**Evidence after fix (terminal capture):**\n\nTest suite (console output — 50 tests pass, including new DREAMS.md assertions and section-replacement test):\n```\n$ OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=4 pnpm test -- extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming-markdown.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming-phases.test.ts\n\n Test Files  2 passed (2)\n      Tests  50 passed (50)\n   Duration  7.07s\nexit code: 0\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** `writeDeepDreamingReport` now always writes the `## Deep Sleep` section to DREAMS.md with the body lines. When separateReports is enabled, the per-phase file is also written. When an existing `## Deep Sleep` section is present (including at file start), it is replaced in-place — other sections preserved, no duplicate headings. When separateReports is disabled, DREAMS.md is still written and `undefined` is returned.\n\n**What was not tested:** Live cron-triggered deep dreaming sweep.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
